# JavaScript Guide — WMPersonal Edition

Concepts you actually encounter in this project, with playgrounds to try them.

---

## 1. async / await

The most important pattern in this project. Almost every backend function is async because it waits for network or DB responses.

```javascript
// BAD — this doesn't wait for the fetch to finish
function getItems() {
  const result = fetch("https://api.warframe.market/v2/items");
  console.log(result); // logs Promise { <pending> }, not data!
}

// GOOD — await pauses until the fetch resolves
async function getItems() {
  const result = await fetch("https://api.warframe.market/v2/items");
  const json = await result.json();
  console.log(json.data.length); // logs actual item count
}
```

**Playground:** paste this in your browser console and run it:
```javascript
async function test() {
  const r = await fetch("https://api.warframe.market/v2/items");
  const j = await r.json();
  console.log("Items:", j.data.length);
}
test();
```

**Trap:** forgetting `await` is the #1 bug. If something logs `Promise { pending }` instead of data, you forgot `await`.

