## 2. try / catch

Always wrap async calls in try/catch. If the network fails or the server returns garbage, your app will crash without it.

```javascript
// BAD — will crash if fetch fails
async function getPrice(slug) {
  const r = await fetch(`/v2/orders/item/${slug}/top`);
  return await r.json();
}

// GOOD
async function getPrice(slug) {
  try {
    const r = await fetch(`/v2/orders/item/${slug}/top`);
    if (!r.ok) throw new Error(`HTTP ${r.status}`);
    return await r.json();
  } catch (err) {
    console.error("Failed:", err.message);
    return null; // return safe fallback
  }
}
```

**Rule:** every function that does a network call or DB query gets a try/catch.

