## 3. Array methods — map, filter, sort

These are used everywhere in this project.

```javascript
const orders = [
  { type: "sell", platinum: 50, user: { status: "ingame" } },
  { type: "buy",  platinum: 40, user: { status: "ingame" } },
  { type: "sell", platinum: 30, user: { status: "offline" } },
];

// filter — keep only online sellers
const onlineSells = orders.filter(o =>
  o.type === "sell" && o.user.status === "ingame"
);
// → [{ type: "sell", platinum: 50, ... }]

// map — extract just the prices
const prices = onlineSells.map(o => o.platinum);
// → [50]

// sort — ascending
prices.sort((a, b) => a - b);
// → [30, 50] (if both were included)
```

**Trap:** `sort()` without a comparator sorts as strings — `[10, 9, 2].sort()` gives `[10, 2, 9]`. Always use `(a, b) => a - b`.

