## 5. Optional chaining (?.) and nullish coalescing (??)

These prevent crashes when data might be missing — very common when dealing with API responses.

```javascript
const order = { item: { slug: "ash_prime_set" }, rank: null };

// BAD — crashes if item is undefined
const slug = order.item.slug;

// GOOD — returns undefined instead of crashing
const slug = order?.item?.slug;

// ?? — use fallback if null or undefined (NOT for 0 or "")
const rank = order.rank ?? "unranked"; // → "unranked" (rank is null)
const plat = order.platinum ?? 0;      // → 0 if missing

// Difference from ||:
const rank2 = order.rank || "unranked"; // → "unranked" even if rank is 0!
// Use ?? when 0 or "" are valid values
```

