## 6. Spread operator (...)

Used for copying and merging objects and arrays.

```javascript
// Copy an array without mutating original
const prices = [50, 30, 70];
const sorted = [...prices].sort((a, b) => a - b);
// prices is still [50, 30, 70], sorted is [30, 50, 70]

// Merge objects
const base = { item: "ash", platinum: 50 };
const extra = { rank: 5, visible: true };
const merged = { ...base, ...extra };
// → { item: "ash", platinum: 50, rank: 5, visible: true }

// In React — add a property to existing state object
setSelected(prev => ({ ...prev, rank: 5 }));
```

