## 7. Express route patterns

```javascript
// Route params — :slug is a variable in the URL
router.get("/:slug/orders", (req, res) => {
  const slug = req.params.slug; // "ash_prime_set" from /ash_prime_set/orders
});

// Query params — ?search=ash&limit=10
router.get("/", (req, res) => {
  const search = req.query.search; // "ash"
  const limit  = req.query.limit;  // "10" (always a string!)
});

// Request body — from POST with JSON
router.post("/fetch", (req, res) => {
  const { url_name } = req.body; // needs express.json() middleware
});

// Always send a response
router.get("/", (req, res) => {
  res.json({ data: [] });      // 200 OK with JSON
  res.status(400).json({ error: "bad request" }); // error
});
```

**Trap:** if you forget to call `res.json()` or `res.send()`, the browser hangs forever waiting for a response.

