## 8. SQLite patterns (better-sqlite3)

```javascript
// SELECT — returns array
const items = db.prepare("SELECT * FROM items WHERE item_name LIKE ?").all("%ash%");

// SELECT one row
const item = db.prepare("SELECT * FROM items WHERE url_name = ?").get("ash_prime_set");
// returns undefined if not found, not null

// INSERT
db.prepare("INSERT INTO items (id, url_name) VALUES (?, ?)").run("abc123", "ash_set");

// Transaction — wrap multiple inserts for speed
const insert = db.prepare("INSERT OR REPLACE INTO items VALUES (?, ?, ?)");
const tx = db.transaction((rows) => {
  for (const row of rows) insert.run(row.id, row.url_name, row.name);
});
tx(itemsArray); // 100x faster than individual inserts
```

**Trap:** better-sqlite3 is synchronous (no await needed). Don't add `await` to DB calls — it won't work.

