## 9. React useState and useEffect

```javascript
// useState — hold and update values
const [items, setItems] = useState([]);   // initial value is []
const [count, setCount] = useState(0);

// Update state (triggers re-render)
setItems([...items, newItem]);
setCount(c => c + 1); // functional update — safer for counters

// useEffect — run code when something changes
useEffect(() => {
  // runs when `search` changes
  getItems(search).then(setItems);
}, [search]); // dependency array

// Empty dependency = run once on mount
useEffect(() => {
  getFavourites().then(setFavs);
}, []);

// Cleanup — cancel timers, close connections
useEffect(() => {
  const timer = setTimeout(() => doSearch(search), 300);
  return () => clearTimeout(timer); // cleanup runs before next effect
}, [search]);
```

**Trap:** putting a function inside the dependency array causes infinite loops. Define it outside useEffect or use useCallback.

