## 10. SSE (Server-Sent Events)

Used in Scanner and Profit tabs for live progress. This is a one-way stream from server to browser.

**Backend — send events:**
```javascript
router.get("/run", (req, res) => {
  res.setHeader("Content-Type",  "text/event-stream");
  res.setHeader("Cache-Control", "no-cache");
  res.flushHeaders();

  // Send a message
  res.write(`data: ${JSON.stringify({ done: 1, total: 10 })}\n\n`);
  // Note: MUST end with \n\n

  // Close when done
  res.end();
});
```

**Frontend — receive events:**
```javascript
const es = new EventSource("http://localhost:3001/api/scanner/run");

es.onmessage = (event) => {
  const msg = JSON.parse(event.data);
  console.log(msg.done, "/", msg.total);
};

es.onerror = () => es.close(); // always close on error
```

**Trap:** SSE connections stay open. Always call `es.close()` when done, or you'll leak connections.

